bgm.name: 魔王魂 旧ゲーム音楽 ダンジョン10

parameters:
(Alright, it seems like no one's around. First, I'll check
out the situation inside the store from here...)

"Ouch, ouch, ouch... damn, the stuff in the warehouse has
toppled over. That's what I get for skimping on cleaning, I
guess."

"Luckily, the goods are safe, so I'll put off cleaning the
warehouse for later. Gotta sell this stuff to those brats
quickly. Kekekekekekeke"

"Phew... looks like he's gone... I'm really glad I wasn't
caught..."

(That shopkeeper mentioned something about the
\c[10]warehouse\c[0]. There might be something useful there,
I should check it out later)
"Let's start by checking out the kitchen first."

"There's an iron pot placed here. It seems like this shop
also serves food."

"Let's make a fuss over this iron pot when we do. It would
be a real problem if it actually caught fire."

(Alright, I've secured both the kindling and fuel! Let's try
to start a fire right away!)

(Yes, I did it! The fire's lit! This should activate the
sprinklers!)

(If my clothes are wet, it'll look suspicious, so I need to
escape from here quickly!)

(This must be the way to the floor, right? I'm curious about
what's inside, maybe I'll take a little peek...?)

*Note: If you select the text in \c[10]red\c[0], it will
result in a \c[10]game over\c[0].
Are you sure about this choice?

(Alright. I'll open the door slowly, trying not to make any
noise...)
"Who the hell are you!? What are you doing there!"
"Crap, I've been spotted! I need to escape quickly!"

"Hey, wait! ...He got away. Did he come to steal medicine? I
need to check the safe quickly. And I should call some
backup too."

I had run into the shopkeeper and, in a panic, fled from the
tavern. A few minutes later, I tried to sneak back into the
tavern, but there were tough-looking men standing guard
around the shop.

It seemed I had become quite suspicious to them, and I
couldn't find even a small gap to slip through. Unable to
get close to the tavern, I had no choice but to return home.

In the end, I never found out if Makoto was even in that
tavern. When I got home, I decided to call her smartphone to
check on her safety.

To my surprise, the call connected immediately. Makoto
seemed to be in a noisy place, and there was a lot of
background noise, but from the sound of her voice, she
seemed to be doing very well.

Just to be sure, I asked where she was, and she said she was
in a different town beyond the neighboring one. Apparently,
she was having dinner with some old friends after a long
time.

Knowing she wasn't in the neighboring town, I felt
completely relieved and ended the call with Makoto without
further discussion. Despite several small inconsistencies, I
failed to notice them until the end.

(No, I better not. You never know when an employee might
come here.)

(No, I better not. You never know when an employee might
come here.)

"This stove hasn't been taken care of at all. I wonder if
the owner of this place is bad at cleaning."
"...Huh? This stove isn't lighting up. Could it be broken?"

(This is a problem... I can't start a fire like this... I
need to find something else that can act as a source of
ignition...)"

"We should be fine with this lighter as a fire source. We
need to find something to burn quickly."
"Let's try burning this oil in the pot next door!"

"This looks like... a fire alarm. If you look closely, there
are sprinklers installed on the ceiling too."

(Sprinklers... Sprinklers, huh... That's it! I've got a
great idea!)

(If I start a small fire here, the sprinklers should
activate and flood the place!)

(That way, they won't be able to continue business, and if
things go well, I might be able to help Makoto escape!)

"Now that I've decided, I need to find something to burn. I
should prepare something that burns well."
(I need to start a fire quickly and rescue Makoto!)

(I've got both the kindling and the fuel ready! All that's
left is to start the fire!)

"There's an empty bottle here. I wonder if it originally had
liquor in it."

"There's an empty bottle here. It might be useful for
something, so I'll take just one."
"I guess I don't need any more empty bottles."
"Let's use this oil to start the fire quickly."

"There might be something useful outside. Should I go out
and check?"

"Ugh, the water stains are terrible. I don't want to wash
dishes in this sink."

"There's a cheap-looking microwave here. It doesn't seem to
be plugged in, but I wonder if it actually works."

"It's a perfectly ordinary refrigerator. There's nothing
suspicious inside."

"It's a perfectly ordinary refrigerator. There's nothing
suspicious inside."

"This locker seems to be used for storing cleaning supplies.
There's a foul smell coming from it... I better not get too
close."
